    "body": "# AiSH 0.3.1 — Windows updater repair\n\nAiSH 0.3.1 repairs the Windows update and application-registration paths introduced in the first stable release.\n\n- Fixed Windows ZIP extraction failing with `Expand-Archive` because the archive and destination arguments were not reaching PowerShell.\n- Fixed Windows Start menu and Installed apps registration using the same unreliable PowerShell argument pattern.\n- Registration now runs through a parameterized PowerShell script with explicit named arguments.\n- Added Windows CI smoke tests for archive extraction with spaces in paths, Installed apps registration, and uninstall cleanup.\n- Future updates from AiSH 0.3.1 and newer can be installed through the normal automatic prompt, `/update`, or `aish --update`.\n\n## Upgrade from 0.2.x or 0.3.0 on Windows\n\nThe faulty updater code is inside the already-installed binary, so affected installations must use the direct installer once:\n\n```powershell\nirm https://github.com/DawnlightLabs/AiSH/releases/latest/download/install.ps1 | iex\n```\n\nAfter that one repair installation, confirm the version:\n\n```powershell\naish --version\n```\n\nFuture releases will be detected and applied through AiSH itself.\n\n## Uninstall\n\n```powershell\naish --uninstall\n```\n",
